title: Quake hits southcentral alaska but apparently damages little
author: Seattle Times Staffseattle Times News Services
text: ANCHORAGE - An earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 5.0 shook Southcentral Alaska yesterday afternoon, but there were few reports of damage.    The Alaska Tsunami Warning Center said it received one report of a television falling from a shelf. There were no injuries reported.    The shallow earthquake was centered 20 miles north of Anchorage.
